, 2006.","meanings":["Apparently a form of <b>Gaynor</b>  adapted to Welsh orthography. It also may have been influenced by the name of the saint commemorated at Llangeinwyr in Glamorgan, known popularly as <i>Llangeinor</i>. Her name is derived from Welsh <i>cain</i> ‘beautiful’ + <i>(g)wyry(f)</i> ‘maiden’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aénor d'Aulnay was born in 1093, in Aulnay, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, her father, Pépin II d'Aulnay, was 27 and her mother, Aldéarde, was 23. She married Jocelin de Lezay in 1117, in Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1139, in Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1093–1139":"1093–1139","1080–1118":"1080–1118","1118–1150":"1118–1150","1066–1098":"1066–1098","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1117":"1117","1139":"1139","1066":"1066","1098":"1098","1150":"1150","1093":"1093","Bef 1118":"enne 1118","1070":"1070","Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Aulnay-de-Saintonge, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Aulnay, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1093–1139":"1093–1139","1080–1118":"1080–1118","1118–1150":"1118–1150","1066–1098":"1066–1098","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1117":"1117","1139":"1139","1066":"1066","1098":"1098","1150":"1150","1093":"1093","Bef 1118":"ennen vuotta 1118","1070":"1070","Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lezay, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska","Aulnay-de-Saintonge, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Aulnay, Charente-Maritime, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska"},"fr":{"1093–1139":"1093–1139","1080–1118":"1080–1118","1118–1150":"1118–1150","1066–1098":"1066–1098","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","1118":"1118","1080":"1080","1117":"1117","1139":"1139","1066":"1066","1098":"1098","1150":"1150","1093":"10